Dear George,  Thanks for post.  Protocols in history,philosophy etc
are interestingly controlled.  There is abook somewhere 1980's called
The Poetics of Philosophy.  Paul Barolsky used the phrase the peotics
of art history in the early 90's and I am aiming at something along
those lines -- have been talking abt a poetics of art history for
quite a while.  Substitute for poetics: "erotics" and you'd have the
philosophers and others really worried.  My feeling is that it might
be easier to work thru anything but professional history mags and go
for poetical marginal ones.
 
