From:         Kevin Killian <dbkk@SIRIUS.COM>
Subject:      40, 50, and 60 year olds
 
Hi, this is really from Kevin and not from Dodie.  Dear Gary Sullivan, I
can't decide how disingenuous you're being when, in describing the horror
of sexual harassment, you ask us how would you like it if some 40, 50, 60
year old guy had his hands down your pants, as though the increasing
decades made the horror more exponential.  As though if the guy was 30 it
wouldn't be so bad and 20 maybe actually okay or groovy.
 
Please clarify on this important point.  Otherwise you're summoning up some
hypothetical bogeyman to scare young poets & playing into a social
construction of a predator (the predator is incredibly old, ancient, even
tho' he may try to look young) (age itself is horror) (the older one gets,
the more vampiric the sexual predator becomes as he needs the young blood
of poets) (the prey, finally, ages much more slowly than the old, 40, 50,
60- year old predator?)
 
Yours-Kevin Killian, aet 42
