Subject:      poem
 
To Not Think of Velvet
 
 
 
I went to 3 rd grade
 
with Joe Biden's daughter
now
 
he rides out through ballots
keeping a mouse
in her lap
 
they're shriveled in color
waiting for your line      here
 
sesames
in the mill
powder balls
on the eye
 
this place
 
four switches
as a heart,
 
run run run
