From:         Loss Glazier <lolpoet@ACSU.BUFFALO.EDU>
Subject:      Carl Gay Obituary
 
FYI, from A University at Buffalo Press release:
----------------------------------------------------------------
Karl Gay, Former Poetry Curator, Dies
 
     "Karl" (Kenneth) Gay, former curator of the University at
Buffalo Poetry Collection, died March 26 in Palma, Majorca, at
age 83.  He was curator from 1968 to 1978 and was secretary to
and friend of Robert Graves for thirty years.  This relationship
provided UB with a sizable collection of Graves' manuscripts and
publications.  Graves, too, lived on Majorca for many years; he
died in 1985.
----------------------------------------------------------------
