Dear Joe,
         Well, we'll all be damned. Some say they're bored and they adopt a
tone, but these are just their effete ways of trying to suppress a necessary
debate, a confrontation with the real issues, of refusing to acknowledge
their fear of communication, of honesty, of lets face it their corruption--I
know I come from New Zealand. They have been touched by power, we all have,
we are all, all of us, miserable stinking sinners. Let us confess, let us
come before the Lord and say, yes Lord, I edited a small magazine. I want
you to know when I say 'small,' that's just because it wasn't mainstream.
You know what I mean by, mainstream? It wasn't without influence i have to
say ...
         Wystan.
