Yay! we're on Spicer again!  First, kudos to Edward Foster for
his monograph on Spicer and Ron Silliman for both the New Sentence
article and his piece in Perelman's *Writing/Talks*.
 
If we are going to talk about power and analogize it to shit,
Spicer had much to say on the subject:
                For you I would build a whole new universe around myself.
                        This isn't shit it is poetry. Shit
                Enters into it only as an image.
                                        -from *Language*
There are only power/ful images.
 
