Wrong, Ed, all poetry has politics, none moreso than the poetry that
claims it has none.
 
Hell, even birds and bees have politics. (In Hawaii, the dominant
ecological niches are fairly unstable. The dominant urban burb of the
1950s, the bulbul, is not that of the late '80s, the mynah. One sees the
hand of polis everywhere....
 
